My review for the series can be found under the "complete 1st season", so I'm just going to talk about the packaging. I really like the 'box' format that matches so well the complete 1st season. Of course, The Rift is not at all profound. Or anything near sophisticated. Some may see this series as trash; well; it is trashy, but it's funny trashy. And unique and surprising. Even the CGI effects are surprisingly well-done. Just enjoy. Like. very well-designed, well-executed trash.

(Oh, this review relates to The Rift's Second Season. There's a movie, too, and a few more seasons.
I doubt there's every been a show like this on cable/satellite. Certainly not on broadcast TV. Are you
an adolescent or a grown-up terminal adolescent? This funny, surprising well-done Sci-Fi spoof is for you.) If you've got a trashy sense of humor you'll give it five stars too.
